# Trivy/tfsec ignores for terraform-aws-elasticache-redis. AVD-prefixed IDs
# (required when a resource is scanned through a module call) + justification.

# AVD-AWS-0104 — "Security group rule allows unrestricted egress to any IP".
#
# Intentional for the cache security group created by this module: ElastiCache
# nodes need outbound for cross-AZ replication, KMS (at-rest key), and
# CloudWatch metrics. Locking egress to an enumerated allow-list would require
# VPC endpoints for every dependency — out of scope for a cache module.
# Inbound IS restricted to the configured source security groups / CIDRs.
#
# Defined at: main.tf  resource "aws_vpc_security_group_egress_rule" "all"
AVD-AWS-0104
